- Speed 13.  - Speed 13 knots.

6
00:01:33,458 --> 00:01:35,127
莽撞鬼
Cowboys.

7
00:02:39,733 --> 00:02:42,027
"醉人者 莫比尔"
"Enchanter, Mobile."

8
00:02:44,488 --> 00:02:48,367
走了很远 叫醒他们!
Well, we're a long way from home. Wake 'em up!

9
00:02:58,043 --> 00:02:59,711
海军!
It's the Navy!

10
00:03:00,837 --> 00:03:02,673
快把旗拿出来!
Quick, put out the flag!

11
00:03:13,684 --> 00:03:14,851
醉人者号!
Enchanter!

12
00:03:15,018 --> 00:03:18,063
这是美国海岸警卫队
This is the United States Coast Guard.

13
00:03:18,230 --> 00:03:21,650
停下来 准备接受调查
Heave to and prepare to be boarded.

14
00:03:35,038 --> 00:03:39,501
醉人者 你是一艘美国船 我们要登船调查
Enchanter, you are a US-flag ship, and we are going to board you.

15
00:03:39,668 --> 00:03:42,129
现在停下来
Heave to now.

16
00:03:53,306 --> 00:03:56,810
叫你的船员到船头
Muster your crew on the bow.

17
00:04:12,534 --> 00:04:14,661
你们俩 到前面去
You two, go forward.

18
00:04:15,996 --> 00:04:18,332
兰德尔 跟我来
Randall, come with me.

19
00:04:23,253 --> 00:04:27,090
- 呆在那儿  - 跪下
- Stay where you are.  - Kneel down.

20
00:04:30,135 --> 00:04:33,555
船长 船长?
Captain. Captain?

21
00:04:34,431 --> 00:04:36,350
高级队长 请说
Go ahead, Senior Chief.

22
00:04:36,516 --> 00:04:42,230
不妙 最好派人拿摄录机来
It's a bad one. I think you'd better send over the video camera.

23
00:04:59,665 --> 00:05:01,792
杰克 进来
Jack, come on in.

24
00:05:04,586 --> 00:05:07,923
- 你桌上的文件有多高?  - 大概这么高
- How high is the pile on your desk?  - About this high.

25
00:05:08,090 --> 00:05:10,467
- 现在是这么高  - 什么情况?
- Now it's this high.  - What have you got?

26
00:05:10,634 --> 00:05:15,639
听过南加勒比海那件事吗? 我要详情
You heard about that business in the South Caribbean? I need the details.

27
00:05:15,806 --> 00:05:19,518
- 何时要?  - 尽快
- By when?  - As soon as you can.

28
00:05:19,685 --> 00:05:23,230
- 好的  - 杰克? 小心点
- OK.  - Jack? Be discreet.

29
00:05:24,898 --> 00:05:28,819
- 什么意思?  - 你会知道
- What do you mean?  - You'll find out.

30
00:05:30,570 --> 00:05:32,656
神神秘秘...
Mysterious...

31
00:05:35,075 --> 00:05:37,119
我爱神秘
I love a mystery.

32
00:05:41,206 --> 00:05:44,710
- 赖 约翰 P  - 让他通过
- Ryan, John P.  - Let him through.

33
00:05:46,712 --> 00:05:49,506
- 这里  - 谢谢
- Here you go.  - Thank you.

34
00:05:49,673 --> 00:05:53,010
- 你认得路吗?  - 认得 谢谢
- You know where you're going?  - Yes. Thank you.

35
00:05:53,760 --> 00:05:57,014
- 在哪里停车?  - 那边
- Where do I park?  - Right over there.

36
00:06:08,316 --> 00:06:10,819
往前面的主要通道
Main passageway, going forward.

37
00:06:10,986 --> 00:06:13,697
主人舱 甲板上有血迹...
Master stateroom, blood on the deck...

38
00:06:13,864 --> 00:06:17,659
找回19枚弹壳
19 cartridges were recovered,

39
00:06:17,826 --> 00:06:23,373
还有发出子弹的两支武器
as well as the two weapons that fired them.

40
00:06:23,540 --> 00:06:30,339
收集到的血液样本跟船员 夏彼得
Blood samples taken were consistent with the crew, Hardin

41
00:06:30,505 --> 00:06:34,468
他的妻子 儿子和女儿都吻合
and his wife and his son and daughter.

42
00:06:35,886 --> 00:06:38,555
床单和枕头上的血迹
I got blood on the sheets and pillow

43
00:06:38,722 --> 00:06:41,224
右舷和左舷架上都有
on both starboard and portside racks.

44
00:06:41,391 --> 00:06:43,393
那儿也有血迹
There's blood there, too.

45
00:06:43,560 --> 00:06:48,231
看来他们是在房里睡觉时被杀
They were killed in their staterooms apparently as they slept.

46
00:06:48,398 --> 00:06:51,360
被拉到甲板再被抛下海
Dragged topside and thrown overboard.

47
00:06:52,736 --> 00:06:57,407
那两个想逃走的人 最后投降被扣押
The two men in custody surrendered after a brief attempt to escape.

48
00:06:57,574 --> 00:07:01,286
我们对那两个被捕的人 知道多少?
What do we know about them? The men in custody?

49
00:07:03,372 --> 00:07:07,459
六次在波哥大贩毒被捕 总统先生
Half a dozen arrests for drug trafficking in Bogota, Mr President.

50
00:07:08,543 --> 00:07:10,045
毒品
Drugs.

51
00:07:11,963 --> 00:07:15,467
怀疑与卡利的毒窟有关 不是麦德林...
Suspected ties to the Cali cartel, not Medellin...

52
00:07:15,634 --> 00:07:19,137
- 哲时 你没事吗?  - ...根据外交部
- You alright, James?  - ...according to DEA.

53
00:07:19,304 --> 00:07:22,015
- 为什么?  - 没什么异样 先生
- Why?  - Nothing exotic, sir.

54
00:07:22,182 --> 00:07:25,727
纯粹是海上劫掠和谋杀 这不是第一次
Straight piracy and murder. It's not the first time.

55
00:07:27,562 --> 00:07:31,024
第一次的事主是我的朋友
It's the first time it was a friend of mine.

56
00:07:32,567 --> 00:07:34,736
是的
Yes, sir.

57
00:07:41,076 --> 00:07:44,496
- 什么事? 你没事吗?  - 没事
- What was that? You alright?  - Yeah.

58
00:07:44,663 --> 00:07:47,457
我三十六小时没有睡过 我有道理吗?
I haven't slept in 36 hours. Did I make any sense?

59
00:07:47,624 --> 00:07:50,377
你说什么? 说笑罢了 做得好
What did you say? Just kidding. Good job.

60
00:07:54,673 --> 00:08:00,012
- 你该开授外交课程  - 如实说出本是我的职责
- You should give diplomacy lessons.  - To call it as I see it is myjob.

61
00:08:00,178 --> 00:08:03,140
- 连他也是你的  - 等我
- And he's yours.  - Wait for me.

62
00:08:07,686 --> 00:08:09,771
关门
Shut the door.

63
00:08:13,066 --> 00:08:18,113
我向美国人民承诺过 要对付毒品问题
I promised the American people I'd do something about the drug problem.

64
00:08:18,280 --> 00:08:20,407
你有
You are.

65
00:08:20,574 --> 00:08:24,578
我们支持哥伦比亚人 对抗那些毒窟...
You support the Colombians' efforts against the cartels...

66
00:08:24,745 --> 00:08:30,375
却全无功效 这些毒贩以为我无能?
And accomplish nothing. Do these drug dealers think we're powerless?

67
00:08:30,542 --> 00:08:36,465
他们可以不断做这种事 却从没有反应?
That they can keep doing this kind of thing, and there's no response ever?

68
00:08:37,632 --> 00:08:41,386
你是否提议采取行动?
Are you suggesting a course of action, sir?

69
00:08:41,553 --> 00:08:47,434
我提议采取的行动一无是处
The course of action I'd suggest is a course of action I can't suggest.

70
00:09:01,782 --> 00:09:05,535
我... 不知道情况会怎么发展
I'm... not sure where that leaves us.

71
00:09:09,373 --> 00:09:13,251
这些毒窟是对美国国家安全
These drug cartels represent a clear and present danger

72
00:09:13,418 --> 00:09:17,255
构成逼在眉睫的危险
to the national security of the United States.

73
00:10:07,180 --> 00:10:09,891
可知道你做了什么事?
Do you know what you've done?

74
00:10:10,058 --> 00:10:11,893
我杀了一个贼
I killed a thief,

75
00:10:12,519 --> 00:10:14,396
我杀了一个偷我的东西的...
a thief who was stealing...

76
00:10:16,898 --> 00:10:18,358
...贼!
...from me!

77
00:10:19,526 --> 00:10:22,529
还有他的妻子 儿女 完全不顾后果
And his wife, and his son, and his daughter,

78
00:10:22,696 --> 00:10:25,240
让他的孩子长大后 在我防不胜防时
apparently with no thought of the consequences.

79
00:10:28,327 --> 00:10:33,623
来替父亲报仇?
Should I let his children avenge their father's death when I least expect it?

80
00:10:34,374 --> 00:10:36,126
他是美国总统的
He was a good friend

81
00:10:36,293 --> 00:10:39,880
好友和政治盟友
and a political ally of the President of the United States.

82
00:10:48,597 --> 00:10:50,807
我不感到出奇
That doesn't surprise me.

83
00:10:51,683 --> 00:10:55,062
- 那该跟你有关  - 他们可以做什么?
- It should concern you.  - What can they do?

84
00:10:55,228 --> 00:10:58,482
来找我? 拘捕我?
Come after me? Arrest me?

85
00:10:58,648 --> 00:11:01,026
你令我害怕
You're scaring me.

86
00:11:02,444 --> 00:11:07,240
可否停下来 跟你谈一件重要事情?
Will you stop long enough for me to tell you something important?

87
00:11:09,785 --> 00:11:11,703
谢谢
Thank you.

88
00:11:14,498 --> 00:11:20,921
你聘请我作你的顾问 我就给你意见
Listen. You pay me to counsel you, and I am counselling you.

89
00:11:21,088 --> 00:11:24,841
我用讯息来保住你的命
I'm keeping you alive with information.

90
00:11:25,008 --> 00:11:27,386
如果你不理会我的劝告
If you disregard my counsel

91
00:11:27,552 --> 00:11:30,931
再这样做生意下去
and keep running your business the way you have been,

92
00:11:31,098 --> 00:11:35,769
不经大脑地 有两件事会发生
with your balls and not your head, two things will happen.

93
00:11:35,936 --> 00:11:39,564
我不干 而你就被杀
I'll quit, and you'll get killed.

94
00:11:50,784 --> 00:11:54,830
你忘了 告诉我你出差的事
You forgot to tell me about your scouting trip.

95
00:11:54,997 --> 00:11:59,251
- 我没有忘记  - 你接触过另一个人 谁?
- No, I didn't.  - You made another contact. Who?

96
00:11:59,418 --> 00:12:02,629
贾斯洛时常问起我的接头人
Castro always asked me about my sources.

97
00:12:02,796 --> 00:12:08,427
- 我总是给他同一个答案  - 贾斯洛给你的酬劳不及我
- I always gave him the same answer.  - Castro didn't pay you what I pay.

98
00:12:08,593 --> 00:12:11,722
这一次不用你出分文
This one will cost you nothing.

99
00:12:13,432 --> 00:12:15,225
女人
A woman.

100
00:12:15,392 --> 00:12:18,020
你利用一个女人
You're using a woman.

101
00:12:24,901 --> 00:12:27,029
它不会浮起来的
It won't float.

102
00:12:28,697 --> 00:12:31,825
- 约翰 你要什么? 多士?  - 烘饼!
- John, what do you want? Toast?  - Waffles!

103
00:12:31,992 --> 00:12:35,537
- 没时间做烘饼了  - 谁见过我的钥匙?
- No time for waffles.  - Anybody seen my keys?

104
00:12:35,704 --> 00:12:38,582
在前门的桌子 上或在你口袋里
Either on the front hall table or in your pocket.

105
00:12:38,749 --> 00:12:41,543
- 我的钥匙在哪里?  - 班戟!
- Where aremykeys?  - Pancakes!

106
00:12:41,710 --> 00:12:44,046
- 多士吧  - 谢谢
- Toast, please.  - Thank you.

107
00:12:44,212 --> 00:12:45,380
再见 爸爸
Bye, Dad.

108
00:12:45,547 --> 00:12:48,675
- 再见  - 它不会浮的!
- Bye, pal.  - It won't float!

109
00:12:48,842 --> 00:12:53,096
它不会浮的 这是艘潜艇 它该在水底的
It's not supposed to float, it's a submarine. It goes under water.

110
00:12:53,263 --> 00:12:54,931
杰克
Jack.

111
00:12:57,267 --> 00:12:59,394
你好?
Hello?

112
00:13:01,480 --> 00:13:02,856
几时?
When?

113
00:13:05,400 --> 00:13:07,736
我以为患上感冒
I thought I had the flu.

114
00:13:07,903 --> 00:13:11,907
如果他们没告诉我 我还以为是感冒
I'd still think so if they weren't telling me otherwise.

115
00:13:13,492 --> 00:13:16,328
他们怎样说?
What are they telling you?

116
00:13:17,245 --> 00:13:23,335
如果我没听错 应是厉害的胰脏癌
Pancreatic cancer of an aggressive nature, if I heard them right.

117
00:13:23,502 --> 00:13:26,713
什么意思?
Well, what does it mean?

118
00:13:27,589 --> 00:13:30,550
我相信我有很大的麻烦
I guess it means I'm in big trouble.

119
00:13:30,717 --> 00:13:35,347
- 他们可否施手术 或者... ?  - 可能
- I mean, can they operate, or...?  - Maybe.

120
00:13:35,514 --> 00:13:40,936
是他们说的 "可能" 我猜是等于说"不"
That's what they said, "maybe", which sounds suspiciously like "no" to me.

121
00:13:41,103 --> 00:13:43,814
那是他们其中一个
There's one of them now.

122
00:13:47,442 --> 00:13:49,236
我还没有死
I'm not dead yet.

123
00:13:50,237 --> 00:13:55,325
我在医院里 即是说我并非在办公室
I am in a hospital, which means that I'm not in my office,

124
00:13:55,492 --> 00:13:57,869
即是说我不知道情况
which means I don't know what's going on.

125
00:13:58,036 --> 00:14:01,039
- 我需要你在那里  - 哪里?
- I need you there.  - Where?

126
00:14:01,206 --> 00:14:05,043
- 在我的办公室里做我的工作  - 等一下...
- In my office, doing my job.  - Wait a minute...

127
00:14:05,210 --> 00:14:08,547
你知道我讨厌掌握不到的情况
I hate not knowing what's going on, you know that.

128
00:14:08,714 --> 00:14:11,717
我不懂做你的工作
I wouldn't know how to do your job, sir.

129
00:14:11,883 --> 00:14:16,179
你一直有参与 也去过白宫
You've been around. You've been to the White House.

130
00:14:16,346 --> 00:14:20,183
- 一次 我讨厌它  - 你没有
- Once. I hated it.  - No, you didn't.

131
00:14:21,268 --> 00:14:25,313
想认识华盛顿的政治吗? 四个字...
Want to know about politics in Washington? Four words.

132
00:14:25,480 --> 00:14:28,316
"当心背后"
"Watch your back, Jack."

133
00:14:33,155 --> 00:14:38,660
波比 你该是第一个知道 或者是第三 四个
Bobby, you should be the first to know, or the third or fourth.

134
00:14:38,827 --> 00:14:42,331
赖将会做署理情报局副局长
Ryan is to be Acting Deputy Director, Intelligence.

135
00:14:42,497 --> 00:14:47,836
那当然是暂时性的委任 直至哲时康复
It will be a provisional appointment, of course, until James recovers.

136
00:14:48,003 --> 00:14:51,631
你向他简报一下 我们对哥伦比亚的援助计划
Get him up to speed on our aid programme to Colombia.

137
00:14:51,798 --> 00:14:56,595
他要说服监督委员会 再拨款七千五百万元
He must talk the Oversight Committee out of another $75 million.

138
00:14:56,762 --> 00:15:00,349
还千万别自暴其短
And not make a complete fool out of himself.

139
00:15:02,267 --> 00:15:04,394
夏彼得被杀的案件又怎样?
What about the Hardin murders?

140
00:15:04,561 --> 00:15:08,315
我在跟进 总统要全力调查
I'm on it. The President's calling for a full-court press.

141
00:15:08,482 --> 00:15:13,528
你们要携手合作了
So, you guys are going to be working together hand in hand.

142
00:15:14,738 --> 00:15:16,907
很好
That's great.

143
00:15:31,838 --> 00:15:36,093
马嘉丽 别动他的东西好了
Margaret, why don't we leave all his things?

144
00:15:36,259 --> 00:15:37,844
好吧 好的
OK, yeah.

145
00:15:50,190 --> 00:15:53,360
赖杰克 我不能相信!
Ryan. I can't believe it!

146
00:15:53,527 --> 00:15:57,197
你指他是个不合作的人?
He's not a team player, is thatwhat you're saying?

147
00:15:57,364 --> 00:15:59,408
他是个白痴
He's a Boy Scout.

148
00:16:00,325 --> 00:16:05,831
一个该死的白痴 相信忠心 廉洁和婚姻
A goddamn Boy Scout. Believes in loyalty, cleanliness and knot-tying.

149
00:16:05,998 --> 00:16:08,083
别管他好了
So leave him out of it.

150
00:16:08,250 --> 00:16:12,295
他当情报局副局长 那会很棘手
He's the Deputy Director of Intelligence. That will be tricky.

151
00:16:12,462 --> 00:16:14,923
他要知道什么?
What does he need to know?

152
00:16:15,090 --> 00:16:21,513
他什么也不必知道 也不会知道什么
Nothing. He needs to know nothing. He's going to know nothing.

153
00:16:21,680 --> 00:16:24,516
我要一份总统授权
I want a copy of the President's authorisation

154
00:16:24,683 --> 00:16:27,602
对毒窟采取新行动的副本
of this new action against the cartels.

155
00:16:28,645 --> 00:16:32,149
- 你要什么?  - 你听到
- You want what?  - You heard me.

156
00:16:33,483 --> 00:16:35,277
他不知情的
He doesn't know about it.

157
00:16:37,237 --> 00:16:43,410
我给你简单地解释 这只是你的行动
Let me explain it to you very simply. This is your deal, not mine.

158
00:16:43,577 --> 00:16:48,665
除非我有书面授权 否则这件事不会进行
Unless I have written authorisation, this thing is over before it begins.

159
00:16:48,832 --> 00:16:53,920
我不想在出问题时 由我来负全责
I'm not going to be the only one left without a chair when the music stops.

160
00:17:34,628 --> 00:17:38,006
"互惠" 一个聪明的代号
"Reciprocity." That's a clever name for it.

161
00:17:38,173 --> 00:17:42,636
报复是个十分危险的动机
Revenge is a very, very, very dangerous motivation.

162
00:17:44,221 --> 00:17:50,394
这个行动你可否应付得来? 我只要知是或否
Are you able to handle this operation or not? I'm looking for a yes or no.

163
00:17:50,560 --> 00:17:53,480
你要卷入一个政治的烂摊子
You're looking for a political mess.

164
00:17:53,647 --> 00:17:56,483
- 是或否?  - 他们要那样?
- Yes or no?  - Is that what they want?

165
00:17:56,650 --> 00:18:01,196
每个首任政府都想获得连任
They want what every first-term administration wants. A second term.

166
00:18:02,531 --> 00:18:05,909
我相信国会还没有批准这事
I don't imagine the boys on the Hill have approved this.

167
00:18:11,581 --> 00:18:13,667
他们有没有?
Have they?

168
00:18:15,544 --> 00:18:18,380
那是否说"不"?
Is that a "no"?

169
00:18:23,593 --> 00:18:25,345
该死
Shit.

170
00:18:26,138 --> 00:18:31,393
我在行动之前 户口里要收到钱
I want the money in my account before I move an inch.

171
00:18:31,560 --> 00:18:33,103
没问题
You got it.

172
00:18:33,270 --> 00:18:35,522
- 我要有通信卫星联系  - 好的
- I need a Comsat link.  - You got it.

173
00:18:35,689 --> 00:18:39,026
- 一支小队  - 你可以有一支部队
- An insertion team.  - You can have a brigade.

174
00:18:39,192 --> 00:18:42,487
只要12个熟识自决式作战的人
Just 12 men who understand discretionary warfare.

175
00:18:42,654 --> 00:18:45,824
特别行动 西班牙语
Special Ops. Spanish speaking.

176
00:18:53,457 --> 00:18:56,209
- 先生 你好吗?  - 很好
- How are you today, sir?  - Very well.

177
00:18:56,376 --> 00:18:59,463
- 请问你到访的目的?  - 公干
- The purpose of your visit?  - Business.

178
00:18:59,629 --> 00:19:02,549
- 你做那一行呢?  - 我卖拖拉机
- What business are you in?  - I sell tractors.

179
00:19:02,716 --> 00:19:05,927
我制造和出售它们
Well, I build them, then I sell them.

180
00:19:06,094 --> 00:19:10,098
- 你会逗留多久?  - 几天
- And how long will you be staying?  - A few days.

181
00:19:37,876 --> 00:19:41,713
我知道很冒险 但还有什么方法?
I know it's a risk, but what's the alternative?

182
00:19:41,880 --> 00:19:46,176
用六千拉德的钴切除视网膜? 不会乐观
Zapping a retina with 6,000 rads of cobalt? Not a pretty picture.

183
00:19:46,343 --> 00:19:49,638
比扩散了的脑瘤好一些
Prettier than a tumour spreading in the cranial sack.

184
00:19:49,805 --> 00:19:53,016
- 她叫什么名字?  - 我正吃饭呢
- What is her name?  - I'm trying to have lunch.

185
00:19:54,184 --> 00:19:57,688
听着... 肚饿吗?
Listen... Hungry?

186
00:19:57,854 --> 00:20:01,733
- 很饿  - 我们别吃午餐
- Starved.  - We could forget about lunch.

187
00:20:01,900 --> 00:20:07,364
- 我们上次也试过 记得吗?  - 我可记得? 你呢?
- We did that last time, remember?  - Do I remember? Do you?

188
00:20:08,699 --> 00:20:12,494
- 不大记得  - 也许我该提你一下
- Vaguely.  - Maybe I should refresh your memory.

189
00:20:14,871 --> 00:20:17,874
- 也许是的  - 你们有台了
- Maybe you should.  - Your table is ready now.

190
00:20:18,041 --> 00:20:21,086
- 我们不要了 我去叫计程车  - 梅丽?
- We don't need it. I'll get a cab.  - Moira?

191
00:20:21,253 --> 00:20:26,758
- 你好吗? 杰克怎样?  - 他很好
- Hi! How are you? How's Jack?  - He's great, just great.

192
00:20:26,925 --> 00:20:29,928
- 还在联邦调查局工作吗?  - 局长办公室
- You still with the FBI?  - The Director's office.

193
00:20:30,095 --> 00:20:32,597
- 那是谁?  - 我的新朋友
- Who was that?  - My new friend.

194
00:20:32,764 --> 00:20:35,684
龙洛鹏
Ser Roberto Landa.

195
00:20:35,851 --> 00:20:39,896
- 他的样子像杰克吗?  - 是吗? 我看得不清楚
- Doesn't he look like Jack?  - Does he? I can't quite see.

196
00:20:40,063 --> 00:20:44,818
- 只差是拉丁籍  - 拉丁杰克? 这个我得看一下
- Only Latin.  - A Latin Jack? This I have to see.

197
00:20:45,819 --> 00:20:48,196
我要走了 再见
I have to go. Bye.

198
00:20:49,948 --> 00:20:54,703
我们知道这不是海上劫掠 海盗会偷船的
Well, we know it's not piracy. Pirates steal boats.

199
00:20:54,870 --> 00:20:59,666
他们身上有案发后翌早去波哥大的机票
They had plane tickets to Bogota the morning afterthe killings.

200
00:20:59,833 --> 00:21:01,501
- 达恩  - 情况怎样?
- Hey, Dan.  - How's it going?

201
00:21:01,668 --> 00:21:05,130
我们正追查着一个动机 莫达恩 联邦调查局
We're sneaking up on a motive. Dan Murray, Bureau.

202
00:21:05,297 --> 00:21:08,175
- 外交部 韦乐帆  - 说过什么?
- Ralph Williams, DEA.  - Said anything yet?

203
00:21:08,342 --> 00:21:12,721
- "我们是清白的 "  - 等检察官给他们提出交易吧
- Yeah. "We're innocent."  - Till the DA offers them a deal.

204
00:21:12,888 --> 00:21:16,308
已经提出了 普通的还是特脆的?
He already has. Regular or extra crispy?

205
00:21:16,475 --> 00:21:20,062
可以是指炸鸡或者那张电椅
Either referring to fried chicken or the electric chair.

206
00:21:20,687 --> 00:21:22,773
你可觉得另有内情?
Are you picturing a hit?

207
00:21:22,939 --> 00:21:27,069
发生在一个受敬重的美籍商人一样?
On a respectable American businessman and his family?

208
00:21:28,070 --> 00:21:31,073
你假设他是受人敬重罢了
You're assuming he's respectable.

209
00:21:39,539 --> 00:21:45,212
我们有便条 信件 信用卡结余单
We have memos, letters, credit card statements,

210
00:21:45,379 --> 00:21:50,801
电话单 你想用来破解他的密码的东西都有
phone bills, everything you could need to break his code.

211
00:21:50,967 --> 00:21:54,012
- 这是什么?  - 高中旧年报
- What's this?  - Old high school yearbook.

212
00:21:54,179 --> 00:21:58,058
- 甜心 足球队...  - 你觉得呢?
- Sweethearts, football team...  - You think?

213
00:21:58,225 --> 00:22:03,105
- 不知道  - 好吧 看我们有什么
- I don't know.  - OK, let's see what we've got.

214
00:22:03,271 --> 00:22:06,358
- 没有奶油?  - 用光了
- No cream?  - There wasn't any.

215
00:22:06,525 --> 00:22:10,320
从生日着手 你的提款机密码一定是你的出生日期
Let's startwith birthdays. Bet your ATM code is your birthday.

216
00:22:10,487 --> 00:22:13,156
- 接近了  - 倒转次序?
- Close.  - In reverse?

217
00:22:15,033 --> 00:22:17,911
他的生日是...
Alright, his birthday is...

218
00:22:19,037 --> 00:22:24,292
那太容易了 是吗? 试一下倒转次序
That would be too easy, wouldn't it? Let's try it in reverse.

219
00:22:24,459 --> 00:22:27,212
错 他太太的?
No. His wife's?

220
00:22:28,255 --> 00:22:30,048
错 他儿子的?
No. His son's?

221
00:22:30,215 --> 00:22:32,551
- 这可以做...  - 几个月
- This could take...  - Months.

222
00:22:32,718 --> 00:22:34,678
儿子的生日倒转 这是给你的
Son's in reverse. This is for you.

223
00:22:37,139 --> 00:22:40,100
错 太太的生日倒转
No. Wife's in reverse.

224
00:22:40,267 --> 00:22:42,477
错 女儿的生日倒转
No. Daughter's in reverse.

225
00:22:42,644 --> 00:22:45,689
你得更改你的提款机密码
You've got to change your ATM code.

226
00:22:48,066 --> 00:22:50,861
不是 不是妻子的生日 不是女儿的生日 什么都不是
No. Wife, daughter. Nothing.

227
00:22:53,322 --> 00:22:54,698
好了
Got it.

228
00:22:54,865 --> 00:22:56,908
进去了!
I got it!

229
00:23:07,294 --> 00:23:11,298
太太的出生月份 女儿的日子 儿子的年份
Wife's birth month, daughter's day, son's year.

230
00:23:11,465 --> 00:23:14,217
但不是倒转次序 抱歉
But not in reverse. Sorry.

231
00:23:21,767 --> 00:23:24,686
印一份给我
Print me out that one.

232
00:23:24,853 --> 00:23:26,772
好孩子
Good boy.

233
00:23:27,439 --> 00:23:31,943
三年前夏彼得收到一大笔外币
Three years ago, Hardin received an infusion of foreign capital

234
00:23:32,110 --> 00:23:37,032
他用来投资在美国二十个大型购物中心
which he invested in 20 major shopping centres in the US.

235
00:23:37,199 --> 00:23:41,828
在经济衰退期间 他获得破纪录的盈利
In the middle of the recession, he posted record profits,

236
00:23:41,995 --> 00:23:46,500
至少对他畏惧的税局来说是这样
at least to the IRS, who he feared more than his own partners.

237
00:23:46,667 --> 00:23:50,962
根据他给他们的股东声明
To them, according to the stockholder statements he was giving them,

238
00:23:51,129 --> 00:23:54,299
那些购物中心的生意并不理想
the shopping centres weren't doing nearly as well.

239
00:23:54,466 --> 00:23:58,804
但他撇去大部分盈利六亿五千万元
But he wasjust skimming most of the profits, $650 million,

240
00:23:58,970 --> 00:24:02,474
还把它存进卢森堡 巴拿马
and putting it in accounts in Luxembourg, Panama

241
00:24:02,641 --> 00:24:04,726
和开曼群岛的户口
and the Cayman Islands.

242
00:24:06,144 --> 00:24:08,230
他们为此而杀他
They killed him for it.

243
00:24:08,397 --> 00:24:10,315
谁?
Who?

244
00:24:10,482 --> 00:24:13,694
- 他的拍档  - 谁是他的拍档?
- His partners.  - Who were his partners?

245
00:24:13,860 --> 00:24:20,242
很明显他替哥伦比亚的毒窟洗钱
It seems clear that he was laundering money for the Colombian drug cartels.

246
00:24:20,409 --> 00:24:26,248
天啊! 我认识了那个人四十年 我们是同学
Jesus! I knew the man for 40 years. We went to school together.

247
00:24:27,165 --> 00:24:29,668
还几乎合作做生意
We almost went into business together.

248
00:24:29,835 --> 00:24:32,462
那该会不错
That would have been good.

249
00:24:34,047 --> 00:24:37,050
传媒会对这事件穷追猛打
The press is going to have a field day with this.

250
00:24:37,217 --> 00:24:41,847
- 这房间以外没有人知道  - 他们总有方法
- No one outside this room knows.  - They will. They always do.

251
00:24:42,014 --> 00:24:45,892
会揭露的 你说得不错 到时我们
It will come up, you're right about that. When it does,

252
00:24:46,059 --> 00:24:51,565
会对你和夏的关系作轻描淡写
we'll downplay your relationship with Hardin somehow.

253
00:24:54,192 --> 00:24:55,902
- 什么?  - 什么?
- What?  - What?

254
00:24:56,069 --> 00:24:59,781
- 我们把它缓和  - 你不同意?
- We'll defuse it.  - Do you disagree?

255
00:24:59,948 --> 00:25:01,450
不
No.

256
00:25:01,616 --> 00:25:06,413
其实是同意 我会用另一种方法
Well, actually, yes. I would go in the other direction.

257
00:25:06,580 --> 00:25:11,960
如果记者问你和夏是否朋友 我会说"好朋友"
If a reporter asked if you and Hardin were friends, I'd say "good friends".

258
00:25:12,127 --> 00:25:16,840
如果他们问你们是否好朋友 我会说"终身好友"
If they asked if you were good friends, I'd say"lifelong friends".

259
00:25:17,007 --> 00:25:22,721
令他们无从入手 没有新闻可报导
Give them no place to go, nothing to report. No story.

260
00:25:24,973 --> 00:25:29,728
我意思是 既然炸弹已经引爆了...
I mean, it's no sense in defusing a bomb after it's already...

261
00:25:31,021 --> 00:25:33,565
...又何须再拆除信管
...it's already gone off.

262
00:25:57,089 --> 00:25:58,632
- 靠!  - 该死!
- Damn!  - Shit!

263
00:26:00,467 --> 00:26:02,052
看到他吗?
Do you see him?

264
00:26:03,303 --> 00:26:07,099
叫你的队员向左移两米
Alright. Move your team two metres to the left.

265
00:26:10,560 --> 00:26:13,271
好了 停
That's it. Stop.

266
00:26:13,438 --> 00:26:18,026
走到那片浅色草堆 狙击手在你的位置
Touch that light-coloured grass. Sniper at your feet.

267
00:26:18,902 --> 00:26:20,737
军士长 这里没什么
Nothing here, Sergeant Major.

268
00:26:20,904 --> 00:26:24,199
- 该死!  - 他很出色
- Damn!  - He is good.

269
00:26:40,966 --> 00:26:44,094
很接近 他怎移动得这么快?
Thatwas close. How's he moving so fast?

270
00:26:49,850 --> 00:26:53,979
我看见他 过来 一直过来 现在跑!
I see him. Come in. Straight in. Now. Run!

271
00:26:55,230 --> 00:26:57,316
一直过来
Keep coming.

272
00:26:58,984 --> 00:27:03,613
停 你的左面 你的左面
Stop. To your left. To your left.

273
00:27:04,281 --> 00:27:08,493
停止 狙击手在你的位置
And stop. Sniper at your feet.

274
00:27:10,162 --> 00:27:12,581
是什么?
What is it?

275
00:27:15,334 --> 00:27:17,085
他在这里吃过午餐
He had lunch here.

276
00:27:18,045 --> 00:27:19,921
麦当劳芝士汉堡包
McDonald's quarter-pounder.

277
00:27:20,088 --> 00:27:22,007
加上奶酪
With cheese.

278
00:27:23,592 --> 00:27:25,093
该死
Damn.

279
00:27:31,141 --> 00:27:33,769
- 该死!  - 四个了
- Damn!  - That's four.

280
00:27:34,895 --> 00:27:38,899
这次你蠃了 出来吧!
Alright, you won this one. Come on out!

281
00:27:40,692 --> 00:27:43,862
士兵 你怎走得这么接近我?
Soldier, how did you get that close to me?

282
00:27:44,029 --> 00:27:49,409
长官 狙击手做个鬼祟的混蛋 来接近导师!
Sniper approached instructor by being a sneaky bastard, Sergeant Major!

283
00:27:49,576 --> 00:27:53,664
蔡维斯 可知道在加州 丢垃圾的罚款?
Do you know the fine for littering in California, Chavez?

284
00:27:53,830 --> 00:27:56,291
知道 长官!
Yes, sir!

285
00:27:58,710 --> 00:28:02,422
我在狙击手训练中见过你 你很出色
I saw you on the sniper course. You looked good.

286
00:28:02,589 --> 00:28:06,259
- 中士 这里受训快完毕吗?  - 是 长官
- Just about finished here, Sergeant?  - Yes, sir.

287
00:28:06,426 --> 00:28:10,389
可渴望带妻儿去度假?
Looking forward to taking some leave with your wife and kids?

288
00:28:11,223 --> 00:28:15,185
- 长官 我没有妻儿  - 你有什么?
- Don't have any wife or kids, sir.  - What do you have?

289
00:28:16,144 --> 00:28:22,651
你很少打电话给别人 也没有多少来往的信件
You don't call anybody often, you don't write or receive many letters.

290
00:28:25,237 --> 00:28:27,990
长官 我可否问你是谁?
Who are you, sir, if I may ask?

291
00:28:28,156 --> 00:28:32,744
祁洛先生和我正策划一项行动 我的组是其中一部分
Mr Clark and I are putting together a mission. My team is a part of it.

292
00:28:32,911 --> 00:28:37,666
你最多会去六个月 如果之后还活着
You'd be gone up to six months, after which, if you're not dead,

293
00:28:37,833 --> 00:28:41,336
你有权选择特种部队内的任务
you'd have your choice of assignments in Special Ops.

294
00:28:58,020 --> 00:29:03,483
...消除一个快将成为另一件丑闻的问题
...defusing an issue that was snowballing into another scandal.

295
00:29:03,650 --> 00:29:07,904
时代日报 报导你和夏是好朋友
"The New York Times" reports that you and Hardin were good friends.

296
00:29:08,071 --> 00:29:12,200
不是好朋友 我们是终身好友
No, not good friends. We were lifelong friends.

297
00:29:12,367 --> 00:29:16,246
是我说的 是我说的
I said that. I said that.

298
00:29:18,206 --> 00:29:20,459
我叫他那样说
I told him to say that.

299
00:29:20,625 --> 00:29:24,338
- 什么?  - 我没有说什么
- What?  - I didn't say anything.

300
00:29:24,504 --> 00:29:28,258
- 但你在想着一件事  - 没有
- But you were thinking something.  - No.

301
00:29:28,425 --> 00:29:33,388
我只是想着 你跟你的同僚的麻烦
I was just distracted by the trouble you were having with your ensemble.

302
00:29:34,306 --> 00:29:39,144
你不是每天都要装作可靠的
Well, it's not every day you have to look trustworthy.

303
00:29:39,311 --> 00:29:43,106
- 谁叫谁说什么?  - 那不重要
- Who told who to say what?  - It's not important.

304
00:29:44,149 --> 00:29:46,860
- 是总统吗?  - 是的
- The President?  - Yeah.

305
00:29:47,027 --> 00:29:51,490
妈说她比总统赚更多钱
Mom says she makes more money than the President.

306
00:29:51,657 --> 00:29:54,993
她可能是对的 再见
She's probably right. Bye.

307
00:30:03,335 --> 00:30:07,547
赖博士 感谢你的资料
Thank you, Dr Ryan, for the information you've shared with us.

308
00:30:08,340 --> 00:30:11,968
- 谢谢 参议员  - 我们一定要帮助哥伦比亚人
- Thank you, Senator.  - We have to help the Colombians

309
00:30:12,135 --> 00:30:16,598
去制止那些毒窟的活动
in their struggle to curtail the drug cartels' activities.

310
00:30:16,765 --> 00:30:22,270
但我不明白 你怎么认为额外的拨款
However, I'm confused. How do you see additional funds

311
00:30:22,437 --> 00:30:25,983
有助这项没有功效的计划?
advancing this programme from the failure that it is?

312
00:30:26,149 --> 00:30:30,487
- 你明白我的意思吗?  - 我不大明白
- You see what I'm getting at?  - No, I'm afraid I don't.

313
00:30:30,654 --> 00:30:34,157
你说这项计划对我们完全有利
You said this effort would be totally benign on our part.

314
00:30:34,324 --> 00:30:38,870
我们的协助只限于供应和建议
Our assistance is limited to supply and advice only.

315
00:30:39,037 --> 00:30:40,789
我已经读过
I've read that.

316
00:30:40,956 --> 00:30:45,127
我也读过一份三十五年前写的类似报告
I've also read a similar finding written 35 years ago

317
00:30:45,293 --> 00:30:49,798
有关在东南亚 一处鲜为人知的丛林
regarding a little-thought-of sliver ofjungle in Southeast Asia.

318
00:30:49,965 --> 00:30:56,096
对不起 你把反毒拨款申请跟越南作比较?
You're comparing our request for anti-drug funds to Vietnam?

319
00:30:56,263 --> 00:31:00,434
我们这个委员会每次被要求时
I'm comparing it to every time a committee such as this is asked

320
00:31:00,600 --> 00:31:05,147
都会对资料不足的申请作出判断
to render judgement based on less than all the facts.

321
00:31:08,066 --> 00:31:11,069
恐怕我不知道怎样回应
I'm afraid I don't know what to say to that.

322
00:31:11,236 --> 00:31:14,448
你可以向我们保证 我们已取得所有事实
You can assure us that we have all the facts.

323
00:31:14,614 --> 00:31:16,158
我认为我有
I thought I had.

324
00:31:16,325 --> 00:31:21,913
那么你可以再向我们保证 这笔额外的拨款
You can further assure us then that this increase in funds

325
00:31:22,080 --> 00:31:25,584
不会被用作秘密的军事行动
will not be used for any covert military action.

326
00:31:25,751 --> 00:31:28,962
我不明白你怎会这样想
I don't know how you're getting to this.

327
00:31:29,212 --> 00:31:32,549
长期的经验
Long experience, sir.

328
00:31:32,716 --> 00:31:34,843
没有军队?
No troops then?

329
00:31:35,010 --> 00:31:40,766
我强调那点 因为我不想出错
I enunciate that clearly because I don't want there to be any mistake.

330
00:31:40,932 --> 00:31:42,642
没有军队
No troops.

331
00:31:43,602 --> 00:31:46,563
你可否说 我以你的话作承诺?
You could say I have your word on that?

332
00:31:46,730 --> 00:31:49,941
你可以那样
You could indeed, because you do.

333
00:32:04,748 --> 00:32:11,421
听着! 除下名牌 把它们传上来
Listen up! Dog tags. Take 'em off, pass 'em forward.

334
00:32:11,588 --> 00:32:17,344
检查口袋里 可以认出身分的东西
Check your pockets for anything that can be used for identification.

335
00:32:25,268 --> 00:32:26,645
到陆地了
We're feet dry.

336
00:32:40,450 --> 00:32:43,662
降落区在望 准备
LZ in sight. Get ready.

337
00:32:43,829 --> 00:32:46,915
祝大家好运 去抓他们吧
Good luck, boys. Go get 'em.

338
00:32:50,794 --> 00:32:53,005
好了 现在降落
OK, let's take her down now.

339
00:33:09,354 --> 00:33:11,690
快 快 快!
Go, go, go!

340
00:34:39,861 --> 00:34:41,530
嘿 波比
Hey, Bob.

341
00:34:43,615 --> 00:34:46,159
- 你好吗?  - 很好
- How you doing?  - Good, sir.

342
00:34:47,160 --> 00:34:49,287
见到你真好
Good to see you.

343
00:34:55,210 --> 00:34:58,714
- 杰克 早  - 赖! 进来吧
- Morning, Jack.  - Ryan! Come on in.

344
00:34:58,880 --> 00:35:01,758
- 认识大家吗?  - 都认识
- Do you know everyone?  - Yes, yes.

345
00:35:01,925 --> 00:35:06,096
- 咖啡? 甜甜圈?  - 麻烦你 黑咖啡
- Coffee? Bagel?  - Coffee. Black.

346
00:35:06,263 --> 00:35:09,349
- 家人好吗?  - 很好
- How's the family?  - Good, sir.

347
00:35:09,516 --> 00:35:13,186
- 我何时可认识另一位赖博士?  - 她很渴望认识你
- When do I meet the other Dr Ryan?  - She's dying to meet you, sir.

348
00:35:13,353 --> 00:35:15,480
很好 坐下
Good, good. Sit down.

349
00:35:17,899 --> 00:35:19,651
谢谢
Thank you.

350
00:35:19,818 --> 00:35:22,029
那么...
So...

351
00:35:22,195 --> 00:35:26,325
- 那些钱仍在那里?  - 先生?
- The cash is still there?  - Sir?

352
00:35:26,491 --> 00:35:30,746
- 在夏彼得的离岸户口  - 六亿五千万元
- In Hardin's offshore accounts.  - $650 million.

353
00:35:30,912 --> 00:35:32,998
- 和零钱  - 和零钱
- And change.  - And change.

354
00:35:33,165 --> 00:35:36,710
- 我们还有那个户口号码  - 是的
- And we have the account numbers.  - Yes, sir.

355
00:35:36,877 --> 00:35:40,839
我们还等什么? 去拿它吧
Well, what are we waiting for? Let's get it.

356
00:35:41,006 --> 00:35:43,884
- 去拿?  - 我们把这东西转过来
- Let's get it?  - Let's turn this thing around.

357
00:35:44,051 --> 00:35:46,219
六亿五千万元和零钱
$650 million and change.

358
00:35:46,386 --> 00:35:51,308
那是政治资金的十倍
It's worth ten times that in political capital.

359
00:35:52,392 --> 00:35:55,062
什么?
What?

360
00:35:55,228 --> 00:36:02,903
夏和那些毒窟的关连 只是一个猜测
Well, this connection between Hardin and the cartels is a theory.

361
00:36:03,070 --> 00:36:05,489
- 猜测?  - 我的猜测
- Theory?  - Atheory of mine.

362
00:36:05,656 --> 00:36:09,326
- 这是个猜测?  - 我知道那些钱是在那里
- It's a theory?  - Well, I know the money is there.

363
00:36:09,493 --> 00:36:14,289
但我不知道其实夏替谁工作
But who exactly Hardin was working for, I don't know.

364
00:36:14,456 --> 00:36:20,170
我们在充公那笔钱之前 要先查证那一点
I think we would have to establish that before we could seize the money.

365
00:36:22,923 --> 00:36:26,218
那么就去那里查证它
So go down there. Establish it.

366
00:36:26,385 --> 00:36:29,054
- 去哪里?  - 哥伦比亚
- Go where?  - Colombia.

367
00:36:30,806 --> 00:36:33,350
谁 我?
Who, me?

368
00:36:36,645 --> 00:36:41,525
我丢下你两个星期 你却踏进一个大陷阱里
I leave you alone for two weeks, and you walk into a big bear trap.

369
00:36:41,692 --> 00:36:43,735
我在想什么?
What was I thinking?

370
00:36:43,902 --> 00:36:50,283
你想令总统留下印像 你不该那样做
You were thinking about impressing the President. You shouldn't do that.

371
00:36:50,450 --> 00:36:53,787
- 十一月  - 一月
- November.  - January.

372
00:36:53,954 --> 00:36:55,747
是去年的
Of last year.

373
00:36:58,709 --> 00:37:03,422
那里有一个人 他以前一直在那里... 祁洛
There's a guy down there, at least he used to be... Clark.

374
00:37:04,381 --> 00:37:06,800
我们认识了很久 是个好人
We go way back. Good man.

375
00:37:06,967 --> 00:37:09,928
如果你遇上麻烦 去找他
If you hit a brick wall, look him up.

376
00:37:11,013 --> 00:37:13,348
纪上将?
Admiral Greer?

377
00:37:13,515 --> 00:37:16,935
- 化疗  - 该死
- Chemotherapy.  - Oh, shit.

378
00:37:17,728 --> 00:37:19,938
又来了
Here we go again.

379
00:37:21,231 --> 00:37:23,567
雷洛培态度怎样?
How's Ritter behaving?

380
00:37:23,734 --> 00:37:27,446
雷一贯作风 没有理会我
Ritter's Ritter. He's leaving me alone.

381
00:37:27,612 --> 00:37:31,783
真的? 像一只鹰般盯着他
Are you sure? Watch him like a hawk.

382
00:37:31,950 --> 00:37:34,202
- 你好吗?  - 很好
- How are you feeling today?  - OK.

383
00:37:34,369 --> 00:37:40,042
我们会替你找个房间 给你一些毛毯 让你躺下
We'll get you in a room, give you warm blankets, get you lying down.

384
00:37:40,208 --> 00:37:43,837
然后我们带你回去房间 休息一下
Then we'll get you back to your room and comfortable.

385
00:38:38,308 --> 00:38:41,645
变量 这是刀子 准备通话 完毕
Variable, this is Knife, stand by to copy, over.

386
00:38:44,606 --> 00:38:47,776
变量 这是刀子 准备通话 完毕
Variable, this is Knife, stand by to copy, over.

387
00:38:47,943 --> 00:38:52,030
刀子 这是变量 你的讯号是五乘五 完毕
Knife, this is Variable, your signal is five by five, over.

388
00:38:55,325 --> 00:38:57,327
无障碍
Clear.

389
00:39:20,892 --> 00:39:23,270
鸡在锅里了 完毕
The chicken is in the pot. Over.

390
00:39:25,105 --> 00:39:28,066
- 煮了它  - 收到
- Cook it.  - Roger that.

391
00:39:44,499 --> 00:39:47,794
亲爱的? 我要迟到了
Honey? I'm late.

392
00:39:48,712 --> 00:39:52,049
- 再见  - 一路顺风
- Bye.  - Have a good trip.

393
00:39:53,133 --> 00:39:56,011
我不会说出来
I'm not gonna say it.

394
00:39:56,178 --> 00:39:58,013
别说
Don't.

395
00:39:58,180 --> 00:40:00,265
小心
Be careful.

396
00:40:28,043 --> 00:40:34,633
本地时间跟华盛顿相同 早上11点16分
Local time is, well, actually, it's the same as Washington, 11:16am.

397
00:40:34,800 --> 00:40:38,303
气温是华氏69度...
Temperature is 69 degrees Fahrenheit...

398
00:40:44,768 --> 00:40:47,062
赖博士!
Dr. Ryan!

399
00:40:56,822 --> 00:41:00,117
外交部特种探员霍珍 你好吗?
DEA Special Agent Jean Fowler. How you doing?

400
00:41:00,283 --> 00:41:02,494
- 首次来波哥大?  - 是的
- First time in Bogota?  - Yeah.

401
00:41:02,661 --> 00:41:07,082
我们别站在这里 让人家向你开枪
Let's not stand here and let someone take a shot at you.

402
00:41:07,249 --> 00:41:09,209
快 长官 我们走吧
Come on, sir, let's go.

403
00:41:23,598 --> 00:41:27,269
- 这两个呢?  - 他们是兄弟
- And these two are?  - They're brothers.

404
00:41:29,980 --> 00:41:34,276
别那样 麻烦你给赖博士多点空气
Don't do that. Give Dr Ryan a bit more air back here, please.

405
00:41:34,443 --> 00:41:36,528
防弹
Bulletproof.

406
00:41:43,785 --> 00:41:47,706
我们没有照片 颜力图的情报人员
We don't have a picture. Escobedo's intelligence officer.

407
00:41:47,873 --> 00:41:51,001
我们也不知道名字 但知道他存在
We don't have a name either, but we know he exists.

408
00:41:52,002 --> 00:41:54,880
那个隐形人?
The invisible man?

409
00:41:55,630 --> 00:41:58,300
慢慢地 用你的手
Gently, gently, with your hands.

410
00:41:58,467 --> 00:42:01,720
雷斯 把双手放在一起
Luis, put your hands together.

411
00:42:02,429 --> 00:42:05,349
不 双手!
No, your hands together!

412
00:42:08,352 --> 00:42:10,854
雷斯 留意导师
Luis, watch the canter.

413
00:42:12,105 --> 00:42:15,108
对了 很好
Yes, very good.

414
00:42:19,237 --> 00:42:20,489
什么事?
Yes?

415
00:42:23,325 --> 00:42:24,951
我们又损失了一架飞机
We lost another plane.

416
00:42:28,288 --> 00:42:29,873
知道了
OK.

417
00:42:32,918 --> 00:42:36,922
- 是谁干的?  - 如果要我猜...
- Who is doing this?  - If I had to guess...

418
00:42:37,089 --> 00:42:40,676
我没有叫你猜 我可以猜
No, I did not ask you to guess. I can guess.

419
00:42:41,551 --> 00:42:44,262
有人泄露给缉毒的警员
Someone has been talking to the drug police.

420
00:42:44,429 --> 00:42:49,601
不可能 如果有人向警方告密 我会第一个知道
Impossible. If anyone spoke to the police, I'd be the first to know.

421
00:42:49,768 --> 00:42:51,853
力图?
Ernesto?

422
00:42:53,271 --> 00:42:58,402
是否我对付了那个美国人后 有人想摧毁我?
Is one of the others trying to ruin me after what I did to the American?

423
00:42:58,568 --> 00:43:04,032
我猜那不是你想像的那样
I guess that wasn't quite the deterrent you thought it would be.

424
00:43:04,199 --> 00:43:06,785
找那个人出来
Find out who it is.

425
00:43:14,292 --> 00:43:18,088
上校 你认为怎样?
What do you make of this, Colonel?

426
00:43:18,255 --> 00:43:20,340
一个机会
An opportunity.

427
00:43:22,467 --> 00:43:24,886
薜波 一个机会
An opportunity, Sipo.

428
00:43:39,109 --> 00:43:42,863
- 午安  - 有口信吗?
- Good afternoon.  - Messages, please?

429
00:43:44,197 --> 00:43:48,785
- 赖博士?  - 祁洛? 抱歉我迟到
- Dr Ryan?  - Clark? Sorry I'm late.

430
00:43:48,952 --> 00:43:51,496
我有十分钟
I've got ten minutes.

431
00:43:53,707 --> 00:43:57,794
我肯定夏跟毒窟有关 那是贩毒的钱
I'm positive Hardin was tied into the cartels. It's drug money.

432
00:43:57,961 --> 00:44:01,882
- 但你证实不到  - 目前为止
- But you can't prove it.  - So far.

433
00:44:03,300 --> 00:44:06,678
- 可介意我问你一个问题?  - 不介意
- Mind if I ask you a question?  - No.

434
00:44:06,845 --> 00:44:12,851
为何你告诉我这些 我已经退出很久了
Why are you telling me all this? I've been out of the game for a long time.

435
00:44:15,062 --> 00:44:20,484
我知道你熟识这个城市 人脉也广
I was told that you were wired, and that you knew the town and people.

436
00:44:20,651 --> 00:44:24,154
- 你是个能手  - 谁告诉你的?
- That you were a player.  - Who told you that?

437
00:44:25,947 --> 00:44:27,866
纪正文
Jim Greer.

438
00:44:29,660 --> 00:44:31,328
他好吗?
How's he doing?

439
00:44:34,456 --> 00:44:37,250
不大好
He's not good.

440
00:44:38,377 --> 00:44:40,295
他患了癌症
He has cancer.

441
00:44:40,462 --> 00:44:42,798
末期
Terminal.

442
00:44:44,633 --> 00:44:48,804
- 他是个好人  - 最好的
- He's a good man.  - The best.

443
00:44:55,060 --> 00:44:57,521
赖博士 你喝咖啡吗?
You a coffee drinker, Dr Ryan?

444
00:45:00,691 --> 00:45:04,569
- 我喜欢喝咖啡  - 试一下连度牌
- Yeah, I like coffee.  - Try the Lindo brand.

445
00:45:04,736 --> 00:45:08,240
- 连度?  - 我相信你会喜欢它
- Lindo?  - I think you'll like it.

446
00:45:14,204 --> 00:45:17,791
总统先生 我有好消息
Mr President, I've got some good news.

447
00:45:17,958 --> 00:45:22,838
你可能认识夏在这里的拍档 颜力图
Hardin's partner here was someone you may know of. Ernesto Escobedo.

448
00:45:23,005 --> 00:45:28,385
- 有理由  - 这是否你另一项猜测?
- Escobedo? It figures.  - Is this another of your theories?

449
00:45:28,552 --> 00:45:34,599
不 这是事实 颜力图像这里的毒枭一样
No, sir. We can call this one fact. Escobedo, like every drug lord here,

450
00:45:34,766 --> 00:45:40,439
也进行合法生意 夏跟这些生意有来往
also had legitimate businesses. Hardin was doing business with these.

451
00:45:40,605 --> 00:45:45,902
其中是进口咖啡 那没什么大不了
Importing, among other things, coffee, which means nothing,

452
00:45:46,069 --> 00:45:52,576
但他以高价购入这些咖啡 每磅六千二百元
but he was paying too much for this coffee. $6,200 a pound.

453
00:45:52,743 --> 00:45:56,288
- 那是昂贵的咖啡  - 我同意
- That's expensive coffee.  - I'd have to agree.

454
00:45:56,455 --> 00:45:59,291
这是好消息 我相信这个可以了
This is good news. I think this does it.

455
00:45:59,458 --> 00:46:03,420
我也有些不大好的消息
Sir, I also have some other news which is not so good.

456
00:46:04,379 --> 00:46:05,964
天啊
Oh, God.

457
00:46:07,299 --> 00:46:12,095
外交部觉得这里的政府 想取得充公了的钱
The DEA feels that the government here would want the seized funds.

458
00:46:12,262 --> 00:46:17,142
- 或是至少一大部分  - 这是我们的钱
- Or at least a large portion.  - This is our money.

459
00:46:17,309 --> 00:46:21,104
- 我们找到的  - 我们可以尝试告诉他们
- We found it.  - We can try telling them that.

460
00:46:21,271 --> 00:46:24,691
尝试? 向他们说或不说也好 我不管
Try? Tell them. Or don't tell them, I don't care.

461
00:46:24,858 --> 00:46:29,571
- 恕我冒犯...  - 告诉他们这是我们的钱
- Sir, with all due respect...  - This is our money, tell them that.

462
00:46:29,738 --> 00:46:34,826
我不懂得怎样说或是从何说起 我不是个谈判专家
I wouldn't know what to say or where to start. I'm not a negotiator.

463
00:46:34,993 --> 00:46:37,245
你可认识政府里的人?
You know someone in their government?

464
00:46:37,412 --> 00:46:40,082
他们的检察总长是我的同学
I went to school with their Attorney General.

465
00:46:40,248 --> 00:46:46,046
谢国士会过来 他来谈判 这是我们的钱
Jacobs will come down. He'll negotiate. This is our money.

466
00:46:46,213 --> 00:46:47,255
谢...
Thank...

467
00:46:48,924 --> 00:46:51,009
谢谢
Thank you.

468
00:46:53,887 --> 00:46:55,973
我讨厌这份工作
I hate this job.

469
00:48:13,842 --> 00:48:16,303
眼睛 上!
Eyes up!

470
00:48:18,430 --> 00:48:20,641
示范组 上!
Demo team, up!

471
00:48:27,731 --> 00:48:29,983
爆炸!
Fire in the hole!

472
00:48:34,488 --> 00:48:37,908
我们来吧! 快走! 快 快 快!
Let's go, let's go! Move out! Go, go, go!

473
00:48:40,619 --> 00:48:41,703
趴下! 趴下!
Down! Down!

474
00:48:59,388 --> 00:49:01,890
谁干的这事死定了
Whoever did this is dead.

475
00:49:03,266 --> 00:49:07,854
谁对我干了这事 死定了!
Whoever did this to me is dead!

476
00:49:08,021 --> 00:49:12,943
你们听到吗? 你们是否听到我说?
Do you hear me? Are you listening to me?

477
00:49:27,749 --> 00:49:31,294
谢先生 你离去前 可否签这个?
Mr Jacobs, could you sign these before you leave?

478
00:49:32,754 --> 00:49:38,010
梅丽 你明天不如请病假
Moira, why don't you call in sick tomorrow?

479
00:49:38,176 --> 00:49:41,555
还有后天 我不会对人说
And the next day. I won't tell anybody.

480
00:49:41,722 --> 00:49:45,183
你虽然不在这里 还有很多工作要做
Even when you're not here there's plenty to do.

481
00:49:45,350 --> 00:49:49,688
- 你的行程表  - 你跟我争论这个?
- Your itinerary.  - You're arguing with me about this?

482
00:49:49,855 --> 00:49:53,525
你太勤快了 再见
You work too hard. Adiy.

483
00:50:32,397 --> 00:50:35,484
- 龙氏公司  - 龙洛鹏
- Landay Landa.  - Roberto Landa, please.

484
00:50:35,651 --> 00:50:40,113
- 我是黄梅丽  - 请等一会
- This is Moira Wolfson.  - One moment, please.

485
00:50:40,280 --> 00:50:44,117
他去了工厂 请等一下
I think he's on the factory floor. Hold on.

486
00:50:49,373 --> 00:50:53,293
- 谁?  - 有一位黄梅丽找你
- Yes?  - A Moira Wolfson is calling.

